sentences.english: Mature olive trees and fire pit in mid ground.
sentences.chinese: 中景是成熟的橄榄树和火塘。

sentences.english: We have planted insectaries between our olive trees to provide year-round habitat for our insectivorous guests.
sentences.chinese: 在橄榄树之间建造昆虫馆提供整年的昆虫栖息地。

sentences.english: Athena produced an olive tree-the symbol of peace and wealth.
sentences.chinese: 雅典娜造了一棵橄榄树，象征和平与财富。

sentences.english: Baal-Hanan the Gederite was in charge of the olive and sycamore-fig trees in the western foothills.
sentences.chinese: 掌管高原橄榄树和桑树的是基第利人巴勒哈南。

sentences.english: In Algeria, children are growing up who have never seen olive trees.
sentences.chinese: 阿尔及利亚的孩子们在成长过程中从未见过橄榄树。

sentences.english: In addition, olive is the sacred tree of Athens, the symbol of peace.
sentences.chinese: 另外，橄榄树是雅典的圣树，是和平的象征。

sentences.english: And the Gentiles,who are not natural branches of the olive tree, have been grafted in their place.
sentences.chinese: 并非橄榄树原枝的外邦人，被接入他们的位置。

sentences.english: The reed and the olive tree were arguing over their steadfastness, strength and ease.
sentences.chinese: 芦苇和橄榄树争论谁坚定强大而又刚中有柔。

definition: pipal tree (Ficus religiosa)/bo fig tree/Bodhi tree (sacred to Buddhism and Hinduism)
